The 2008 Preakness Stakes was the 133rd running of the Preakness Stakes. The race time was 6:15pm EDT and was televised in the United States on the NBC television network. Big Brown, the 1-5 favorite, was the winner by 5 lengths over Macho Again.[1] The Maryland Jockey Club reported total attendance of 121,876, this is recorded as second highest on the list of American thoroughbred racing top attended events for North America in 2008.[2] The 133rd Preakness Stakes Payout Schedule Winning Owner: IEAH Stables & Paul Pompa, Jr. Winning Breeder: Monticule (KY)
